OPSAI ASSISTANT AWS MVP — VERIFIED END-TO-END BUILD, UI, TESTING AND CLEANUP GUIDE
Steps 1–22 + Permissions, Cost and Cleanup | AWS Region: us-east-1 | Updated: 17 July 2026

IMPORTANT NOTES
1. Use an IAM user or IAM/SSO role for all steps. Do not build the Knowledge Base with the AWS root user.
2. Complete all CloudShell steps with the same IAM identity and in the same Region.
3. The commands use dynamic discovery wherever possible. Do not copy another account's bucket, Agent ID or Alias ID.
4. Amazon Bedrock Agents Classic stops accepting new customers on 30 July 2026. This guide remains valid for accounts that activated Agents Classic before that date. Existing customers can continue using it.
5. The Infrastructure Assets, Approvals and HR Portal pages use sample browser data. They do not connect to or modify a real Kubernetes/RKE2 cluster or HR system.
6. The right-side globe photograph and other illustrations are decorative UI assets and do not represent live operational data.
7. The two HR quick buttons open local HR Portal searches; they do not query the Bedrock Knowledge Base.
8. CORS is temporarily open during initial testing and is restricted to the Amplify URL later in this guide.

