Appendix B — Three-Day Cost and Pricing Model
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

The architecture is mainly serverless. There is no EC2 server or database running continuously.

The main usage-based services are:

- Amazon Bedrock model inference.
- Titan Text Embeddings document and query embeddings.
- Amazon S3 and S3 Vectors storage and requests.
- AWS Lambda requests and execution duration.
- API Gateway HTTP API requests.
- Amplify Hosting storage and data transfer.
- CloudWatch Logs ingestion and retention.

Rough three-day MVP guide

Idle or almost no use:
Usually very low cost.

Light demonstration with about 100 questions:
Often below ₹50, depending on prompt size, answer size, Bedrock agent calls and existing free-tier usage.

Heavier demonstration with hundreds of questions:
Cost can increase because Bedrock is charged by model usage and the agent may make multiple model calls.

Recommended safety budget:
₹300 for three days.

This is a planning estimate, not an AWS quotation. Taxes, invoice currency conversion, Region, model tier, log volume and account free-tier eligibility can change the final amount.

Important cost controls:

- Use Amazon Nova Lite, not a more expensive model.
- Keep answers concise.
- Keep the Knowledge Base small.
- Do not enable Bedrock Provisioned Throughput.
- Do not attach AWS WAF unless required.
- Do not enable unnecessary debug logging.
- Use CloudWatch log retention.
- Delete unused Amplify applications.
- Run the cleanup after the event.
- Create an AWS Budget alert, for example USD 5.

Always verify the latest prices in the AWS Pricing Calculator and the official service pricing pages before production use.

